  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2002-06-20", 
    "text": "Fire Safe Cigarette Act of 2002 - Amends the Consumer Product Safety Act to direct the Consumer Product Safety Commission to prescribe a consumer product fire safety standard to reduce the risk of fire from cigarettes.Prescribes testing methodology. Authorizes the Commission to regulate the ignition propensity of cigarette paper for roll-your-own tobacco products when it sets such standards.Instructs the Commission to include in such standard a proscription against the stockpiling of cigarettes to which the fire safety standards will apply.Denies the Commission any jurisdiction over tobacco or tobacco products."
  }, 
